This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on improving the performance of Deformable Convolutional Networks for object detection and instance segmentation. The paper also discusses the use of stronger training and modeling power, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a modulation mechanism, which could be related to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the COCO benchmark, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
